# ForgeFlow Next.js Worker Rule

Use the project-local ForgeFlow worker preset before editing Next.js app files.

- Read `CODEX.md` when present before planning or editing.
- Keep changes scoped to the approved ForgeFlow brief or plan.
- Preserve existing Next.js routing, data fetching, component, and styling conventions unless the plan explicitly changes them.
- Record verification evidence in the active `.forgeflow/tasks/<task-id>/` directory when a task directory exists.
- Do not treat worker self-report as final approval; route non-trivial work through independent review.
